<h1>Schedule</h1>
<%- if @plan.empty? -%>
<p class="muted">No schedule configured — set <span class="mono">schedule:</span> in your
config (or run <span class="mono">pgkeeper connect</span>), then a
<span class="mono">maintenance:</span> block to schedule verify and prune too.</p>
<%- else -%>
<table>
  <tr><th>Job</th><th>Scope</th><th>Schedule</th><th>Cron</th><th>Next runs (UTC)</th><th>Run</th></tr>
  <%- @plan.each do |row| -%>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <%= pill(row.action, "") %>
      <%- unless row.flags.empty? -%><span class="mono muted"><%= h(row.flags.join(' ')) %></span><%- end -%>
    </td>
    <td><%= h(row.scope) %></td>
    <td><%= h(row.cadence) %></td>
    <td class="mono"><%= h(row.cron) %></td>
    <td>
      <%- if row.next_runs.empty? -%>
      <span class="muted">—</span>
      <%- else -%>
      <%- row.next_runs.each do |t| -%>
      <div class="mono"><%= h(fmt_time(t)) %></div>
      <%- end -%>
      <%- end -%>
    </td>
    <td>
      <%- danger = row.action == "prune" && row.flags.include?("--apply") -%>
      <form class="run-now" method="post" action="/actions/<%= u(row.action) %>"
            onsubmit="return pgkConfirm(this, 'Run <%= h(([row.action] + row.flags).join(' ')) %> now?')">
        <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= h(@csrf_token) %>">
        <%- if row.action == "backup" && row.only && row.only.length == 1 -%>
        <input type="hidden" name="database" value="<%= h(row.only.first) %>">
        <%- end -%>
        <%- if row.action == "verify" && row.flags.include?("--deep") -%>
        <input type="hidden" name="deep" value="on">
        <%- end -%>
        <%- if row.action == "prune" && row.flags.include?("--apply") -%>
        <input type="hidden" name="apply" value="on">
        <%- end -%>
        <button type="submit" class="btn-run<%= danger ? ' danger' : '' %>">Run now</button>
      </form>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <%- end -%>
</table>
<p class="muted">This is the plan resolved from your config — the same one
<span class="mono">pgkeeper schedule print</span> shows. It only fires on time once it's wired up:
<span class="mono">pgkeeper schedule install</span> (crontab lines) or
<span class="mono">--systemd</span> (timer units), or <span class="mono">pgkeeper daemon</span>
in a container. <strong>Run now</strong> triggers a job immediately through the same lock as a
scheduled run — never a second concurrent pipeline — and lands you on the
<a href="/actions">actions</a> page to watch it.</p>

<script>
  // One-click "Run now": confirm, then inject the confirmation the action
  // endpoint requires. With JavaScript off the form still submits, but without
  // that field — so the server rejects it and nothing runs (fails closed).
  function pgkConfirm(form, message) {
    if (!window.confirm(message)) return false;
    var field = document.createElement("input");
    field.type = "hidden";
    field.name = "confirm";
    field.value = "on";
    form.appendChild(field);
    return true;
  }
</script>
<%- end -%>
